First Lady Jill Biden and President Joe Biden addressed the National Education Association (NEA) during their annual meeting. Jill Biden, a teacher herself, discussed how she spends her summer preparing for the upcoming school year by reading, going to the beach, and thinking about curriculum changes. She emphasized the importance of education in shaping the future and highlighted the Biden administration's commitment to investing in schools and supporting educators. President Biden thanked educators for their hard work and discussed the administration's efforts to provide support for schools and address the teacher shortage. He also emphasized the need for gun safety legislation and criticized attempts to ban books. The Bidens expressed their gratitude to educators and pledged their commitment to supporting them.